{
  "texts": [
    "The first two experiments were done to evaluate the model in two cases; the first was to detect the benign and malignant masses, while the other aimed to detect the existence of the mass regardless it was benign or malignant.",
    "Considering the results of Tables 6 and 7, it can be deduced that the model showed better results at detecting the masses regardless of its type.",
    "The performance enhanced significantly by almost ' 13% in terms of mAP.",
    "Moreover, this approach improved the number of the true detected masses from 19 to 22 with less FP and FN, as shown in Tables 6 and 7.",
    "Table 7 also shows that the input image size affected the model's performance as the higher resolution showed better mAP."
  ]
}